Accusatives plural in -is from i- stems are usual. The rules given in Fleckeisen, p. 13, generally apply.

In many instances the best MSS present the superlative in -umus, but there are many others in which they have -imns without any variant. The two forms seem to have co-existed (cf. Bramb. p. 14). The question is so complicated that in many particular instances it would be difficult to decide between these forms, especially as I did not take down all the Ms evidence on this point from the commencement of my collation. Ι have therefore thought it better to spell in all cases with -imus.
